begin
reserve k for Nat;
reserve m for Nat;
reserve n for Nat;
theorem
Th11: (((1 < m & ( ( n * k ) mod m ) = ( k mod m )) & k,m are_relative_prime ) implies ( n mod m ) = 1)
proof
assume that
A1: 1 < m
and
A2: ( ( n * k ) mod m ) = ( k mod m )
and
A3: k,m are_relative_prime ;
consider t2 being Nat such that A4: k = ( ( m * t2 ) + ( k mod m ) ) and ( k mod m ) < m by A1,NAT_D:def 2;
consider t1 being Nat such that A5: ( n * k ) = ( ( m * t1 ) + ( ( n * k ) mod m ) ) and ( ( n * k ) mod m ) < m by A1,NAT_D:def 2;
( ( n * k ) - ( 1 * k ) ) = ( m * ( t1 - t2 ) ) by A2,A5,A4;
then A6: m divides ( k * ( n - 1 ) ) by INT_1:def 3;
reconsider n,m as Integer;
m divides ( n - 1 ) by A3,A6,INT_2:25;
then consider tt being Integer such that A7: ( n - 1 ) = ( m * tt ) by INT_1:def 3;
n = ( ( m * tt ) + 1 ) by A7;
then ( n mod m ) = ( (1 qua Integer) mod m ) by EULER_1:12
.= 1 by A1,NAT_D:14;
hence thesis;
end;
